      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f022c054c90229956c16f3605399a75b2501ebb6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-23 17:00:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nSome comments:\n- instead of adding lru_cache_drain() before every call to ext4_mb_cache_init(), why not put this inside ext4_mb_cache_init()?\n- it doesn't seem right that we would need to call lru_cache_drain(). Do we have proper calls to mark_page_accessed() in the mballoc functions?\n- this kind of patch should really be pushed upstream to get feedback. If it is a performance problem with ldiskfs it is also true for ext4.\n- we are trying to get rid of kernel patches, and this patch will prevent building on an unpatched kernel and on SLES. The use of lru_cache_drain() should have a configure check. \n\nFor a long time I've thought it would be better to avoid putting large files into cache by reducing readcache_max_filesize. This would help avoid cache pressure on the bitmaps, as well as on the inode table and other metadata.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "9b8d579956988698cfd2dd39e30ff56f8bd84dc7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-23 19:03:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nAndreas,\n\nmark_page_accessed() is NOP without a calling a lru_add_drain().\nbecause find_or_create_page put a page to the lru pagevec batch, and wait \nuntil pagevec full to move to real LRU.\nmark_page_accessed() just mark a page referenced (NOT accessed) for these pages (PageLRU() is false).\nBUT shrink_inactive_list() have call lru_add_drain() so move pages from lru pagevec to inactive list, when shrink_inactive_list found that page and kill.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "ebc3d3557ba7d3d3fd9ccca1e6cb5444f994ed63",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-23 23:10:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThis definitely sounds like a problem to discuss on the linux-ext4 mailing list and fix upstream, instead of just patching ldiskfs.  Once we figure out what is the best solution for the upstream kernel, we can patch it into ldiskfs, and hope that it will also be included in RHEL and SLES so we don't have to patch this for every kernel in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "b572eb519a5db370cd01ee6122be8e45eab49e99",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-03-24 04:55:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/cf80ba82-943b-11e2-ba8c-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "ff98cc51b16af88800f1286c7eb10b9588e0b2c2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-03-24 07:00:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/30d7d1c6-944b-11e2-93c6-52540035b04c).  Ran 20 tests.  4 tests failed: replay-ost-single, conf-sanity, replay-single, sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "7d557ae2e89304c9ed8c985c2a5664a407119b12",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-24 08:22:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nAndres,\n\nyou are correct, that is kernel side problem - but until patch will be accepted by upstream want to put it's in kernel/ldiskfs patches to have better performance.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "f6941cf0b40e209d2734fb1e6c9db07d435bb4cf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-25 00:54:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI'm not against including a patch for the kernel and ldiskfs, but:\nA) post on linux-ext4 to discuss problem and see if there is a better fix\nB) need to make a configure check if kernel is patched with EXPORT_SYMBOL(lru_add_drain)\nC) move lru_add_drain() calls into ext4_mb_init_cache()",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "694f2c8085851a912bee483ca077b75af8b7781e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-25 09:20:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nsetting -1 until some discussion on linux-ext4 - patching the kernel doesn't look very good, imho.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "495d1444e586f25260d3f291562f0bc7031b78c3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 136,
        "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
        "email": "alexey.lyashkov@hpe.com",
        "username": "shadow"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-26 07:19:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nWe may write a patch without patching a kernel, just use a shake_page(page, 0) as replace to lru_add_drain().\nvoid shake_page(struct page *p, int access)\n{\n        if (!PageSlab(p)) {\n                lru_add_drain_all();\n                if (PageLRU(p))\n                        return;\n                drain_all_pages();\n                if (PageLRU(p) || is_free_buddy_page(p))\n                        return;\n        }\n\nbut it's adds some overhead as call drain lru pages at all CPU's.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "67ae39e0d088d1075598382102be261b6b14a122",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-27 17:38:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nAs previously mentioned, I'm not against a kernel patch if it is detected by configure if the EXPORT_SYMBOL() is present or not. That allows the optimized behavior if the kernel is patched, and the current behavior if unpatched.\n\nI saw the email to linux-ext4, so I'll try to get some action on this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "301d96edacc98de068f865a683cbd53a8804c84a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-17 15:59:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nI saw that the upstream kernel has fixed the mark_page_accessed() code to correctly reference the buddy bitmap pages in the LRU.\n\nI'd be happy to get an updated version of this patch that backports that fix to RHEL6 and SLES11SP2 kernels.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "d441ac49018f461c4af708399e3d0b5d47399484",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 142
      },
      "date": "2013-09-27 15:39:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Abandoned\n\nthe solution needs to be backported from vanilla kernel",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    }
  ],
